@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Index";
}

<link href="~/css/index.css" rel="stylesheet">

<header>
    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-md navbar-dark fixed-top bg-dark">
        <img src="/images/ucontroller-small.png" width="80" /><span class="uconfy_logo uconfy_logo_white">&micro;Confy</span>
        <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#navbarCollapse" aria-controls="navbarCollapse" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
            <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarCollapse">
            <ul class="navbar-nav mr-auto">
            </ul>
            <form class="form-inline mt-2 mt-md-0">
                <button onclick="document.location.href = '/webapp/#/'; event.preventDefault();" class="btn btn-outline-success my-2 my-sm-0" type="submit">Login</button>
                <button onclick="document.location.href = '/webapp/#/signup'; event.preventDefault();" class="btn btn-outline-success my-2 my-sm-0 signup_btn" type="submit">Signup</button>
                <button onclick="document.location.href = '/webapp/#/?demologin=1'; event.preventDefault();" class="btn btn-outline-success my-2 my-sm-0 signup_btn" type="submit">Demo Account</button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </nav>
</header>

<main role="main">

    <div id="myCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">
        <ol class="carousel-indicators">
            <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
            <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="1"></li>
            <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="2"></li>
        </ol>
        <div class="carousel-inner">
            <div class="carousel-item active">
                <img class="first-slide" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAHd3dwAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" alt="First slide">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="carousel-caption text-left">
                        <h1>Logging</h1>
                        <p>You can send logs from your &micro;Controller to &micro;Confy, which gives you a better debugging experience.</p>
                        <p><a class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" onclick="document.location.href = '/app#signup'; event.preventDefault();" href="#" role="button">Sign up today</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img class="second-slide" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAHd3dwAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" alt="Second slide">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="carousel-caption">
                        <h1>Configuration</h1>
                        <p>Your &micro;Controller device can fetch config variables from &micro;Confy, so that you can re-configure your &micro;Controller device without re-deploying your code.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img class="third-slide" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAHd3dwAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" alt="Third slide">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="carousel-caption text-right">
                        <h1>Diagnostics</h1>
                        <p>Your &micro;Controller device can send diagnostics data to &micro;Confy, so that you can monitor your device's health.</p>
                        <p>(upcoming feature)</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#myCarousel" role="button" data-slide="prev">
            <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
        </a>
        <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#myCarousel" role="button" data-slide="next">
            <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
        </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Marketing messaging and featurettes
    ================================================== -->
    <!-- Wrap the rest of the page in another container to center all the content. -->

    <div class="container marketing">

        <!-- Three columns of text below the carousel -->
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <img class="rounded-circle" src="~/images/plus-flat.png" alt="Generic placeholder image" width="140" height="140">
                <h2>Register</h2>
                <p>Register your device on &micro;Confy - you will receive a DeviceID &amp; API Key pair that is unique to your microcontroller based device.</p>
                <p><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#" onclick="document.location.href = '/app#signup'; event.preventDefault();" role="button">Sign up &raquo;</a></p>
            </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <img class="rounded-circle" src="~/images/firmware-icon.png" alt="Generic placeholder image" width="140" height="140">
                <h2>Deploy</h2>
                <p>Upgrade your microcontroller's code, use &micro;Confy lib and deploy it to your device.</p>
                <p><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://github.com/akos-sereg/esp32-uconfy-component/wiki" target="_blank" role="button">View Docs &raquo;</a></p>
            </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <img class="rounded-circle" src="~/images/terminal.png" alt="Generic placeholder image" width="140" height="140">
                <h2>Monitor</h2>
                <p>Check the logs, diagnostics, telemetry of your device on &micro;Confy.</p>
            </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
        </div><!-- /.row -->
        <!-- START THE FEATURETTES -->

        <hr class="featurette-divider">

        <div class="row featurette">
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <h2 class="featurette-heading">Motivation: <span class="text-muted">Configuring Primary and Fallback wifi.</span></h2>
                <p class="lead">
                    I wanted to make sure that my microcontroller-based devices are portable and can be used in <b>different wifi zones</b> (eg. moving to
                    another flat), without the need of re-deploying firmware. So I created this web app where I can register my devices
                    and manage their configurations. My devices' wifi connections are being managed by &micro;Confy library, which allows
                    the devices to use pre-defined wifi zones. As a result, I <b>do not have to touch</b> the embedded software once my device
                    is created.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-5">
                <img class="featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto" src="~/images/moving.png" width="200" alt="Moving the device to different wifi zone">
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="featurette-divider">

        <div class="row featurette">
            <div class="col-md-7 order-md-2">
                <h2 class="featurette-heading">Monitoring your device. <span class="text-muted">Feed logs into &micro;Confy.</span></h2>
                <p class="lead">
                    If your microcontroller-based device has wifi access, it makes sense to feed logs into &micro;Confy. This way you can
                    always take a look into your device's internal behaviour, which makes debugging easier. Eg. you do not have to connect your device
                    with your computer to debug it via wire (usb cable).
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-5 order-md-1">
                <img class="featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto" src="~/images/monitoring.png" width="200" alt="Logging">
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="featurette-divider">

